During the exam, which Edith is working at very hard, she receives a series of phone calls, right in succession, which she tries to ignore but eventually she gets concerned about. She asks the professor if she can step into the hallway to see what the phone calls are about, thinking they are an emergency. She calls the number back and it is the dry cleaner urgently asking her how she wants it cleaned so that they don't ruin the scarf. As she's in the hallway, she hears screams and a gun firing. One student, overcome by stress of the exam and twisted from decades reading alt-right forums on the internet, disgusted by what he sees as the collapse of Western Enlightenment, opens fire on what he calls his "Cultural Marxist" professor. Edith, having been in the hallway, hears the hail of bullets strike in time for her to sprint away and call the campus security. She ends up being safe, even though her professor and many of her classmates are killed in the rampage.
